The Network File System (NFS) is a client/server application that lets a computer user view and optionally store and 
   update files on a remote computer as though they were on the user's own computer
   There are 4 versions of nfs - nfsv2, nfsv3, nfsv4 ,NFSv2
   
   commands:
   sudo apt-get -y install nfs-kernel-server

   sudo systemctl enable nfs-kernel-server
   
   mkdir emo_dir (create directory for mounting)
     touch ab.txt
     cat /etc/exports
     sudo exportfs -ra

sudo apt-get -y install nfs-common

sudo mount -t nfs 127.0.01:/home/system/emo_dir /home/system_directory
